In [[knitting]], '''picking up stitches''' means adding stiches to the [[knitting needle]] that were previously [[binding off (knitting)|bound off]] or belong to the [[selvage (knitting)|selvage]].

Picking up stitches is commonly done in knitting [[garment]]s, e.g., in knitting the collar or cleeves.  Picking up stitches is also essential for [[entrelac|entrelac knitting]].

